A 22-year-old man was caught by the police for allegedly sexually assaulting a five-year-old girl at his house in Chandrayangutta on Tuesday night.The accused, Abdul Khader, who works as salesman at a groceries store in Mir Alam Mandi, lured the girl who stays adjacent to his house and sexually abused her.The child complained about it to her parents who approached the police on Wednesday. He was detained late on Wednesday night.A case has been registered.Teacher killed in accidentA school teacher died in a road accident at Mailardevpally on Thursday morning. The victim, Mohammed Khaja Moinuddin (51) of Gulshan Iqbal colony in Chandrayangutta, worked as a teacher at ZPHS at Muchinthal in Shamshabad. At around 8.30 a.m. when the man was going to the school on his motorcycle, a private bus hit his bike from behind at Laxmiguda crossroads. “Moin fell on the road and came under the front tyre of the bus. Death was instant for him,” Inspector Mailardevpally S. Venkat Reddy said.